item.title: Milwaukee Tour
item.description: Known for its beer, brats, baseball, and stunning lakefront scenery, Milwaukee is a town with a lot more sights than most travelers realize. During the course of this Milwaukee sightseeing tour, see the city's famous City Hall and tour the Milwaukee Art Museum. Learn the history of this city by the lake and view its exceptional homes, and since tours are capped at 14 people you're ensured a personalized experience.

image.alt: Milwaukee Tour

item.title: Discover Iconic Milwaukee Tour
item.description: Swap the big bus tours for a crowd-free experience. Traveling in an open-air, five-seater electric vehicle, you'll thoroughly explore the historic city of Milwaukee, from popular tourist destinations to some hidden gems that most visitors miss. As you travel, your guide will fill you in on Milwaukee's rich and exciting history. This tour has different lengths to suit your schedule.

image.alt: Discover Iconic Milwaukee Tour

item.title: Milwaukee Walking Food Tour With Secret Food Tours
item.description: The Midwestern city of Milwaukee is known for its beer and cheese and this walking food tour gives you a taste of the best. Join a small group and enjoy a walk through "Brew City" to sample a number of beers and regional snacks. Learn about the 19th-century Germanic population that immigrated to the area and its influence on today's local cuisine.

image.alt: Milwaukee Walking Food Tour With Secret Food Tours

item.title: Boat Cruise- Sunset Live Music Cruise
item.description:
Indulge in a serene and relaxing evening as we cruise through the tranquil waters of Green Bay and witness one of Door County's magnificent sunsets, accompanied by live music to set the perfect ambiance. Our route will vary depending on the day, to ensure the best possible sunset viewing opportunities.
As you sit back, relax, and take in the awe-inspiring scenery, be sure to have your camera handy to capture those unforgettable moments. With the gentle breeze in your hair and the sun setting on the horizon, this is the perfect way to unwind and appreciate the natural beauty of Door County.
So why not join us for an evening of serenity, live music, and stunning sunsets? Come and experience the magic of Door County as we sail through the calm waters of Green Bay, and cherish the memories of this enchanting experience for years to come.
See Door County from the water!

image.alt: Boat Cruise- Sunset Live Music Cruise

item.title: Downtown Madison E-Bike Guided Tour
item.description: Make the most of your visit with the help of a guide who’ll take you to see some of the best of Madison by bike. Whether you want to get the lay of the land when you arrive in town for the first time, or you’re a local looking to learn more about the history of your city, this informative tour has something for everyone.

image.alt: Downtown Madison E-Bike Guided Tour

item.title: Trolley Pub Public Tour
item.description:
Check out the best Madison has to offer on this two-hour pedal powered pub crawl. You'll stop by some of the hottest spots in Downtown Madison on our mobile bar on wheels. Tours are BYOB with our on-board cooler and you can play your own music.
The tour is the most fun way to experience the city and our trained guides help have a blast.

image.alt: Trolley Pub Public Tour

item.title: Cave Point Kayak Tour
item.description: Wisconsin's Door County sits on a narrow peninsula between Green Bay and Lake Michigan. With this kayak tour, safely explore the thousand-year-old caves and scenic waterways of Cave Point County Park and Whitefish Dunes State Park with a guide. Along with a tandem kayak and a life vest, your tour also includes an introductory paddle lesson. Plus, choose from multiple times to best suit your schedule.

image.alt: Cave Point Kayak Tour

item.title: Door County Day Trips: Sightseeing Top to Bottom
item.description: Discover the best of Door County, Wisconsin as you embark on a day trip to the area’s top landmarks. Join a small group and spend the day exploring outdoor areas like Whitefish Dunes State Park, Cave Point County Park, and Ellison Bluff. Other points of interest include Sturgeon Bay, Egg Harbor, Sister Bay, Ephraim, and Baileys Harbor.

image.alt: Door County Day Trips: Sightseeing Top to Bottom

item.title: Peninsula State Park Views Segway Tour w/ Private Tour Option
item.description: Explore Door County’s Peninsula State Park on a fun Segway tour with a small group. Effortlessly glide through the park’s roadways for unparalleled views of the forest, Green Bay, and nearby islands. Learn about the region from your tour guide and enjoy plenty of stops to take photos of your day.

image.alt: Peninsula State Park Views Segway Tour w/ Private Tour Option

item.title: West Islands & Eagle Bluff Lighthouse Cruise
item.description: Experience Door County’s most relaxing—yet wild—side on this scenic sightseeing cruise. With your captain narrating the way, you’ll see a side of Wisconsin most don’t realize even exists: tiny islands speckled with thousands of shorebirds; historic lighthouses; towering, forested bluffs hanging high above the water; and more. All you have to do is sit back and take it in (and bring your camera or binoculars).

image.alt: West Islands & Eagle Bluff Lighthouse Cruise

item.title: Boat Cruise - North Shore to Death’s Door Crossing
item.description: Jutting into Lake Michigan, Door County has hundreds of miles of great views—and they’re all greatest from the water. You’ll get to sit back and enjoy them on this leisurely cruise along Sister Bay's north shore, witnessing towering bluffs, bird rookeries, tiny islands, and more. Your captain will also regale you with tales of the area’s fishing heritage and wild shipwrecks, deepening your appreciation of this gorgeous Wisconsin spot.

image.alt: Boat Cruise - North Shore to Death’s Door Crossing

item.title: Hearthstone Historic House Museum Admission Ticket
item.description: Take a step back in time on this docent-led tour of the Hearthstone Historic House Museum in Appleton. It’s the first house in the world that was lit by a Thomas Edison central hydroelectric power station; see the original fixtures inside the house for yourself. As you tour the rooms and educational exhibits, your docent shares fascinating stories about Appleton history.

image.alt: Hearthstone Historic House Museum Admission Ticket

item.title: Brew City Ghosts: Macabre Milwaukee By US Ghost Adventures
item.description: Unveil the dark history of Brew City with this ghost tour of the city’s most haunted locations. Meet your guide for a ghoul-fueled stroll through the heart of Milwaukee to take in spirit-infested historic hotels, theaters, and even skyscrapers. Be entertained by bone-chilling ghost stories and tales of paranormal activity as you delve into Milwaukee’s ghoulish past.

image.alt: Brew City Ghosts: Macabre Milwaukee By US Ghost Adventures

item.title: Shakers Original Historical Ghost Tour
item.description: One of the most haunted bars in the nation, Shaker’s Cigar Bar—a Milwaukee institution—has a history as wild as its ghostly encounters. On this small-group tour, you’ll explore behind the scenes, hearing stories about the Capone brothers and Jeffrey Dahmer, the bar's cemetery and brothel past, and more. Bring your camera, sure, but beware of what you might catch on film.

image.alt: Shakers Original Historical Ghost Tour

item.title: Cream City Cannibal: Jeffery Dahmer Walking Tour
item.description: As seen on the BBC, yes, that BBC. this tour is so gruesome, that NBC called it the " Tour of Terror" and NETFLIX picked this tour as one of the eight most unique adventure tours in the world for a new series: "Dark Tourist". Not for the faint of heart! The Cream City Cannibal Tour has been featured in the John Borowski film; Serial Killer Culture and used by regional University Psychology and Criminal Justice departments. Walk in the exact footsteps of cannibalistic serial killer Jeffrey Dahmer, where he poached 7 of his 17 victims. Rife with tales of caution, psychological dissection, and terrifying details, the Cream City Cannibal is not for the feint of heart. Outdoor, Rain or Shine.

image.alt: Cream City Cannibal: Jeffery Dahmer Walking Tour

item.title: Skip the Line: Museum Admission Ticket - Grohmann Museum
item.description: Prebook this Grohmann Museum Skip-the-Line Admission Ticket to bypass the lines at the museum on the busy school campus and head inside to explore its collections and exhibits. The museum showcases the art of labor, engineering, and human achievement while and offering a unique display you won’t find anywhere else. This admission ticket is perfect for groups that want to explore but who are also on a budget.

image.alt: Skip the Line: Museum Admission Ticket - Grohmann Museum

item.title: The Grand Walk: A Self-Guided Audio Tour through Milwaukee
item.description: The home of American lager and once a rival to Chicago in size, Milwaukee’s history and preeminence may not be as obvious as it once was—unless you look. With this self-guided audio tour, you’ll travel down Brew City’s most opulent drag, from the Milwaukee Public Library to the Milwaukee Art Museum. Across 150 years of history and plenty of steps, you’ll get a guided-tour experience without any of the crowds.

image.alt: The Grand Walk: A Self-Guided Audio Tour through Milwaukee

item.title: Fish Creek Town Segway Tour w/ Private Tour Option
item.description: See the natural splendor of Fish Creek in Wisconsin’s beloved Door County from the comfort of a Segway on this fun and unique guided tour. You’ll see all the charming town’s highlights, from the scenic Niagara Escarpment to Peninsula State Park to the tony Millionaire’s Row to the Alibi Dock Marina bobbing with boats. Finish at the stunning Sunset Beach State Park and understand why it has that name if you go at the right time of day.

image.alt: Fish Creek Town Segway Tour w/ Private Tour Option

item.title: Haunted History Trolley Tour in Wisconsin Dells
item.description: The Wisconsin Dells may be known for fun and games, there's a darker side you'll discover on this after-dark haunted history tour. Climb aboard the vintage trolley for a ride to the most spooky spots in town, like the Spring Grove Cemetery and a restaurant known for its ghost sightings. Get out to explore at each stop, and be sure to check your photos for mysterious orbs and other paranormal signals.

image.alt: Haunted History Trolley Tour in Wisconsin Dells

item.title: Sea Kayaking in Door County, Wisconsin
item.description:
Unique kayak tours that offer a higher level of comfort on the water with luxury kayaks that are stable and easy to paddle.
Single kayaks for all our guests. Stay drier in our clean, modern sea kayaks. We are the only tour company offering high end sea kayaks for tours, all the other companies in the area only offer sit-on-top kayaks.
Smaller tour group sizes means a more personalized experience for you with no need to feel rushed or left behind.
Modern sea kayaks with deluxe comfort seats for the most enjoyable kayak tour ride in Door County.
Ditch the crowded tours for something different this summer and explore Door County with certified Naturalist & Sea Kayak Instructor. This tour of Door Bluff is ideal for beginners.

image.alt: Sea Kayaking in Door County, Wisconsin

item.title: Milwaukee Private or Public Pedal Tavern Tour
item.description:
Tour an upcoming and historic neighborhood just on the outside of downtown like a local would! Local and friendly drivers to take you along our well-known route.
Experience a unique way to travel around with pedal power! Fun and different experience on the tavern as you cheer your crew, and make memories and friends along the scenic river and downtown! 21+ Tour

image.alt: Milwaukee Private or Public Pedal Tavern Tour

item.title: Peninsula Park Caves Scenic Boat Tour
item.description: This tour takes you along the beautiful shoreline of Peninsula State Park. You will learn about the area's rich history and see sights like Eagle Bluff Lighthouse, built in 1848. The highlight of the tour gets you up close to Eagle Bluff directly below the point where Eagle Tower sits in the park. Here, you'll see evidence of how this body of water was once part of the Silurian Sea by viewing the caves high above in the rock formations. We'll then cruise past Horseshoe Island, known as one of the safest natural harbors in the Great Lakes. While heading back to Fish Creek, we will talk about the 4 Strawberry Islands and the distant Chambers Island.

image.alt: Peninsula Park Caves Scenic Boat Tour

item.title: Madison Ghosts: Haunts, Spirits, and Poltergeists Walking Tour
item.description:
Ready to uncover Madison’s spookiest secrets? Join us for a thrilling and fun walking ghost tour through the city’s most haunted historic spots! Led by expert local guides—Madison’s official haunted history gurus—you’ll hear real, chilling tales of the city’s dark past and the spirits that still roam today.
Explore iconic sites and hidden gems on Madison’s #1 guided ghost tours and haunted pub crawls. Experience spine-tingling stories nightly, revealing centuries of wicked history and visits to haunted buildings and bars. Wander haunted streets after dark and discover local legends, from infamous witch trials to scandalous tragedies.
Learn why Madison is one of America’s most haunted cities as you stroll through its historic district. Tours cover about a mile of ghostly ground, showcasing authentic tales and deep connections to the eerie past. Get ready for a hair-raising adventure on this captivating journey through Madison’s haunted history!

image.alt: Madison Ghosts: Haunts, Spirits, and Poltergeists Walking Tour

item.title: Bayfield Ghost Walk
item.description: Hear about all the haunts of Bayfield on this group walking tour, where your guide tells you all about the ghoulish stories surrounding the city. You tour the city, stopping at cursed houses, places haunted with spirits, and hear stories about infamous men in white, the cursed courthouses, and much more.

image.alt: Bayfield Ghost Walk
